                <script nonce="uwzdamULF/BHQMuDaM/gsrU11BPNH7OWRNW1PU0izow=" type="text/javascript">window.__DATA__ = {"jiraIssueCollectorId":"ee87e716","page":{"document":[{"type":"markdown","content":"\n# Deprecation notice - Basic authentication with passwords\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"aui-message note\">\n    \u003cdiv class=\"icon\">\u003c/div>\n    \u003cp>\n        \u003cstrong>The deprecation period for this functionality has ended. From June 3rd, 2019, we will be progressively disabling the usage of this authentication method. \u003c/strong>\n    \u003c/p>\n    \u003c/br>\n    \u003cp>If you are using a REST endpoint in Confluence with basic authentication, update your app or integration to use API tokens, OAuth, or Atlassian Connect.\n    \u003c/p>\n    \u003cbr/>\n\u003c/div>\n\nAtlassian has introduced support for [API tokens] for all Atlassian Cloud sites as a replacement \nfor [basic authentication] requests that previously used a password or primary credential for an Atlassian \naccount.\n\nBasic authentication with passwords is now deprecated and will be removed in 2019 per [Atlassian REST API policy].\n\n## What is changing?\n\nIf you currently rely on a script, integration, or application that makes requests to Confluence Cloud with basic authentication, you should update it to use basic authentication with an API token, OAuth, or Atlassian Connect as soon as \npossible.\n\n[Learn more about creating API tokens].\n\n## Why is Atlassian making this change?\n\nUsing primary account credentials like passwords outside of Atlassian's secure login screens creates security risks for our \ncustomers. API tokens allow users to generate unique one-off tokens for each app or integration. If needed, users can easily revoke API tokens.\n\nFurthermore, as customers adopt features like two-factor authentication and SAML, passwords may not work in all cases. Atlassian designed API tokens as an alternative for Atlassian accounts in organizations that use these features.\n\n## Which APIs and methods will be restricted?\n\nFor the following APIs and pages, all requests using basic authentication with a non-API token credential will return 401 (Unauthorized) after the deprecation period:\n\n* Confluence Cloud public REST API\n* All Confluence Cloud web pages\n\n[API tokens]: https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/api-tokens-938839638.html\n[basic authentication]: /cloud/confluence/basic-auth-for-rest-apis/\n[Atlassian REST API policy]: class="sc-cxZfpC ctHTAJ" width="192"><div class="sc-jEdsij kGIpwq"></div></div></div><div class="aui-message note">
            <div class="icon"></div>
            <p>
                <strong>The deprecation period for this functionality has ended. From June 3rd, 2019, we will be progressively disabling the usage of this authentication method. </strong>
            </p>
            <br/>
            <p>If you are using a REST endpoint in Confluence with basic authentication, update your app or integration to use API tokens, OAuth, or Atlassian Connect.
            </p>
            <br/>
        </div>
        <p>Atlassian has introduced support for <a href="https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/api-tokens-938839638.html" target="_blank">API tokens<style data-emotion-css="hakgx8">.css-hakgx8{display:inline-block;-webkit-flex-shrink:0;-ms-flex-negative:0;flex-shrink:0;line-height:1;width:16px;height:16px;}.css-hakgx8 > svg{overflow:hidden;pointer-events:none;max-width:100%;max-height:100%;color:var(--icon-primary-color);fill:var(--icon-secondary-color);vertical-align:bottom;}.css-hakgx8 > svg stop{stop-color:currentColor;}@media screen and (forced-colors:active){.css-hakgx8 > svg{-webkit-filter:grayscale(1);filter:grayscale(1);--icon-primary-color:CanvasText;--icon-secondary-color:Canvas;}}.css-hakgx8 > svg{width:16px;height:16px;}</style><span role="img" aria-label="Follow" style="--icon-primary-color:currentColor;--icon-secondary-color:var(--ds-surface, #FFFFFF)" class="css-hakgx8"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="presentation"><g fill="currentColor" fill-rule="evenodd"><path d="M11.031 7A1.03 1.03 0 0010 8.036a1.05 1.05 0 001.044 1.045l3.121.014.014 3.121a1.05 1.05 0 001.045 1.044 1.03 1.03 0 001.036-1.035l-.019-4.161a1.053 1.053 0 00-1.045-1.045L11.035 7h-.004z"/><path d="M13.364 8.292l-7.072 7.071a1.002 1.002 0 000 1.415c.39.39 1.024.39 1.415 0l7.071-7.071A1.002 1.002 0 0014.071 8a1 1 0 00-.707.292z"/></g></svg></span></a> for all Atlassian Cloud sites as a replacement
        for <a href="/cloud/confluence/basic-auth-for-rest-apis/" target="_self">basic authentication</a> requests that previously used a password or primary credential for an Atlassian
        account.</p>
        <p>Basic authentication with passwords is now deprecated and will be removed in 2019 per <a href="/platform/marketplace/atlassian-rest-api-policy/" target="_self">Atlassian REST API policy</a>.</p>
        <h2 id="what-is-changing-">What is changing?<span role="presentation" class="heading-anchor-wrapper"><button class="sc-bNQFlB bCHUsn"><style data-emotion-css="1ncnk3i">.css-1ncnk3i{display:inline-block;-webkit-flex-shrink:0;-ms-flex-negative:0;flex-shrink:0;line-height:1;width:24px;height:24px;}.css-1ncnk3i > svg{overflow:hidden;pointer-events:none;max-width:100%;max-height:100%;color:var(--icon-primary-color);fill:var(--icon-secondary-color);vertical-align:bottom;}.css-1ncnk3i > svg stop{stop-color:currentColor;}@media screen and (forced-colors:active){.css-1ncnk3i > svg{-webkit-filter:grayscale(1);filter:grayscale(1);--icon-primary-color:CanvasText;--icon-secondary-color:Canvas;}}.css-1ncnk3i > svg{width:24px;height:24px;}</style><span role="img" aria-label="copy" style="--icon-primary-color:#6B778C;--icon-secondary-color:var(--ds-surface, #FFFFFF)" class="css-1ncnk3i"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="presentation"><g fill="currentColor" fill-rule="evenodd"><path d="M12.856 5.457l-.937.92a1.002 1.002 0 000 1.437 1.047 1.047 0 001.463 0l.984-.966c.967-.95 2.542-1.135 3.602-.288a2.54 2.54 0 01.203 3.81l-2.903 2.852a2.646 2.646 0 01-3.696 0l-1.11-1.09L9 13.57l1.108 1.089c1.822 1.788 4.802 1.788 6.622 0l2.905-2.852a4.558 4.558 0 00-.357-6.82c-1.893-1.517-4.695-1.226-6.422.47"/><path d="M11.144 19.543l.937-.92a1.002 1.002 0 000-1.437 1.047 1.047 0 00-1.462 0l-.985.966c-.967.95-2.542 1.135-3.602.288a2.54 2.54 0 01-.203-3.81l2.903-2.852a2.646 2.646 0 013.696 0l1.11 1.09L15 11.43l-1.108-1.089c-1.822-1.788-4.802-1.788-6.622 0l-2.905 2.852a4.558 4.558 0 00.357 6.82c1.893 1.517 4.695 1.226 6.422-.47"/></g></svg></span></button></span></h2>
        <p>If you currently rely on a script, integration, or application that makes requests to Confluence Cloud with basic authentication, you should update it to use basic authentication with an API token, OAuth, or Atlassian Connect as soon as
        possible.</p>
        <p><a href="https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/api-tokens-938839638.html" target="_blank">Learn more about creating API tokens<style data-emotion-css="hakgx8">.css-hakgx8{display:inline-block;-webkit-flex-shrink:0;-ms-flex-negative:0;flex-shrink:0;line-height:1;width:16px;height:16px;}.css-hakgx8 > svg{overflow:hidden;pointer-events:none;max-width:100%;max-height:100%;color:var(--icon-primary-color);fill:var(--icon-secondary-color);vertical-align:bottom;}.css-hakgx8 > svg stop{stop-color:currentColor;}@media screen and (forced-colors:active){.css-hakgx8 > svg{-webkit-filter:grayscale(1);filter:grayscale(1);--icon-primary-color:CanvasText;--icon-secondary-color:Canvas;}}.css-hakgx8 > svg{width:16px;height:16px;}</style><span role="img" aria-label="Follow" style="--icon-primary-color:currentColor;--icon-secondary-color:var(--ds-surface, #FFFFFF)" class="css-hakgx8"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="presentation"><g fill="currentColor" fill-rule="evenodd"><path d="M11.031 7A1.03 1.03 0 0010 8.036a1.05 1.05 0 001.044 1.045l3.121.014.014 3.121a1.05 1.05 0 001.045 1.044 1.03 1.03 0 001.036-1.035l-.019-4.161a1.053 1.053 0 00-1.045-1.045L11.035 7h-.004z"/><path d="M13.364 8.292l-7.072 7.071a1.002 1.002 0 000 1.415c.39.39 1.024.39 1.415 0l7.071-7.071A1.002 1.002 0 0014.071 8a1 1 0 00-.707.292z"/></g></svg></span></a>.</p>
        <h2 id="why-is-atlassian-making-this-change-">Why is Atlassian making this change?<span role="presentation" class="heading-anchor-wrapper"><button class="sc-bNQFlB bCHUsn"><style data-emotion-css="1ncnk3i">.css-1ncnk3i{display:inline-block;-webkit-flex-shrink:0;-ms-flex-negative:0;flex-shrink:0;line-height:1;width:24px;height:24px;}.css-1ncnk3i > svg{overflow:hidden;pointer-events:none;max-width:100%;max-height:100%;color:var(--icon-primary-color);fill:var(--icon-secondary-color);vertical-align:bottom;}.css-1ncnk3i > svg stop{stop-color:currentColor;}@media screen and (forced-colors:active){.css-1ncnk3i > svg{-webkit-filter:grayscale(1);filter:grayscale(1);--icon-primary-color:CanvasText;--icon-secondary-color:Canvas;}}.css-1ncnk3i > svg{width:24px;height:24px;}</style><span role="img" aria-label="copy" style="--icon-primary-color:#6B778C;--icon-secondary-color:var(--ds-surface, #FFFFFF)" class="css-1ncnk3i"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="presentation"><g fill="currentColor" fill-rule="evenodd"><path d="M12.856 5.457l-.937.92a1.002 1.002 0 000 1.437 1.047 1.047 0 001.463 0l.984-.966c.967-.95 2.542-1.135 3.602-.288a2.54 2.54 0 01.203 3.81l-2.903 2.852a2.646 2.646 0 01-3.696 0l-1.11-1.09L9 13.57l1.108 1.089c1.822 1.788 4.802 1.788 6.622 0l2.905-2.852a4.558 4.558 0 00-.357-6.82c-1.893-1.517-4.695-1.226-6.422.47"/><path d="M11.144 19.543l.937-.92a1.002 1.002 0 000-1.437 1.047 1.047 0 00-1.462 0l-.985.966c-.967.95-2.542 1.135-3.602.288a2.54 2.54 0 01-.203-3.81l2.903-2.852a2.646 2.646 0 013.696 0l1.11 1.09L15 11.43l-1.108-1.089c-1.822-1.788-4.802-1.788-6.622 0l-2.905 2.852a4.558 4.558 0 00.357 6.82c1.893 1.517 4.695 1.226 6.422-.47"/></g></svg></span></button></span></h2>
        <p>Using primary account credentials like passwords outside of Atlassian&#x27;s secure login screens creates security risks for our
        customers. API tokens allow users to generate unique one-off tokens for each app or integration. If needed, users can easily revoke API tokens.</p>
        <p>Furthermore, as customers adopt features like two-factor authentication and SAML, passwords may not work in all cases. Atlassian designed API tokens as an alternative for Atlassian accounts in organizations that use these features.</p>
        <h2 id="which-apis-and-methods-will-be-restricted-">Which APIs and methods will be restricted?<span role="presentation" class="heading-anchor-wrapper"><button class="sc-bNQFlB bCHUsn"><style data-emotion-css="1ncnk3i">.css-1ncnk3i{display:inline-block;-webkit-flex-shrink:0;-ms-flex-negative:0;flex-shrink:0;line-height:1;width:24px;height:24px;}.css-1ncnk3i > svg{overflow:hidden;pointer-events:none;max-width:100%;max-height:100%;color:var(--icon-primary-color);fill:var(--icon-secondary-color);vertical-align:bottom;}.css-1ncnk3i > svg stop{stop-color:currentColor;}@media screen and (forced-colors:active){.css-1ncnk3i > svg{-webkit-filter:grayscale(1);filter:grayscale(1);--icon-primary-color:CanvasText;--icon-secondary-color:Canvas;}}.css-1ncnk3i > svg{width:24px;height:24px;}</style><span role="img" aria-label="copy" style="--icon-primary-color:#6B778C;--icon-secondary-color:var(--ds-surface, #FFFFFF)" class="css-1ncnk3i"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="presentation"><g fill="currentColor" fill-rule="evenodd"><path d="M12.856 5.457l-.937.92a1.002 1.002 0 000 1.437 1.047 1.047 0 001.463 0l.984-.966c.967-.95 2.542-1.135 3.602-.288a2.54 2.54 0 01.203 3.81l-2.903 2.852a2.646 2.646 0 01-3.696 0l-1.11-1.09L9 13.57l1.108 1.089c1.822 1.788 4.802 1.788 6.622 0l2.905-2.852a4.558 4.558 0 00-.357-6.82c-1.893-1.517-4.695-1.226-6.422.47"/><path d="M11.144 19.543l.937-.92a1.002 1.002 0 000-1.437 1.047 1.047 0 00-1.462 0l-.985.966c-.967.95-2.542 1.135-3.602.288a2.54 2.54 0 01-.203-3.81l2.903-2.852a2.646 2.646 0 013.696 0l1.11 1.09L15 11.43l-1.108-1.089c-1.822-1.788-4.802-1.788-6.622 0l-2.905 2.852a4.558 4.558 0 00.357 6.82c1.893 1.517 4.695 1.226 6.422-.47"/></g></svg></span></button></span></h2>
        <p>For the following APIs and pages, all requests using basic authentication with a non-API token credential will return 401 (Unauthorized) after the deprecation period:</p>
        <ul>
        <li>Confluence Cloud public REST API</li>
        <li>All Confluence Cloud web pages</li>
